    {
      "number": 41,
      "title": "Adoption of and Amendments to the California Wildland-Urban Interface (WUI)",
      "action": "M/S/C (Blackaby/Humbert) to adopt the second reading of Ordinance No. 7,991\u2013N.S. and approve the recommendations below. \u2022 Thank the members of the WUI Vegetation Code Workgroup for their efforts, including their very detailed and thoughtful recommendations in 2 letters back to Council; \u2022 Refer to the City Manager the items in the Workgroup's letter (including non- combustible trash & recycling bins, wood shake roofs, wire mesh size for Vector Control, and facilitating permitting of metal privacy screens to replace privacy hedges) to then return to Council with specific proposals for consideration; and \u2022 After the State Board of Forestry finalizes its Zone Zero regulations, request that the City Manager reconvene the Workgroup to help provide feedback on the differences between the state and local vegetation management laws (if any), such that the City Manager can then report back to City Council with an update within 90 days of the state's new rules. Vote: Ayes \u2013 Kesarwani, Taplin, Tregub, O\u2019Keefe, Blackaby, Lunaparra, Humbert, Ishii; Noes \u2013 None; Abstain \u2013 None; Absent \u2013 Bartlett. Tuesday, December 2, 2025 ANNOTATED AGENDA Page 20 Action Calendar \u2013 Public Hearings",
